init_text: A woman has been dating guy after guy, but it never seems to work out. She's unaware that she's actually been dating the same guy over and over; a shapeshifter who's fallen for her, and is certain he's going to get it right this time.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: She asks him if he would like some dessert.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He keeps saying how much he appreciates her.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: She realizes she's starting to feel uncomfortable.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: She looks in his eyes, and sees only one thing: hunger.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: She has fallen for the man with no face, the one who is unable to be real or true.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: In fact, she has every reason to believe that it won't.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He asks her if she's breaking up with him.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: She realizes that he has no idea what she's talking about.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The realization that she's dating the same person over and over again is staggering.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: She has seen this act before.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: She turns around, a bit spooked.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: She reads about shapeshifters and knows, in her heart, that this is what she's been dating.
